Moss Beach Video SW Interface

This interface is used between the Moss Beach Video SW and the
IOS Linecard Controller (LCC).


Parameters of an video input session
------------------------------------
  - session id
  - input mode: unicast or multicast
    - for unicast:
      - dest UDP port
      - IP address (?)
    - for multicast:
      - source and dest IP addresses
      - dest UDP Port
      - multicast mode: SSM or ASM (?)
  - session type: SPTS remux, MPTS passthru, MPTS remux, data injection


Parameters of an video output session
-------------------------------------
  - input session id
  - QAM id
  - session type: same as in input session
    - for SPTS remux:
      - program number
    - for MPTS passthru: ?
    - for MPTS remux
  - filtered PID list ?




For unicast traffic, the dest UDP port is used to identify the input session.
A UDP port map will be used for unicast mapping.

For multicast traffic, the source and dest IP address, and the dest UDP port,
are used to identify the input session.  A hashed multicast lookup table will
be used for multicast mapping.

Both the unicast and multicasting lookup table will need to indicated whether
an entry is configured, and if so, the info of the corresponding session.

A session may be in one of the following states:
  - configured, but not started: session struct not created
  - active: session struct created

The session struct is created when the session traffic is first detected.



Unicast Session Config / Unconfig
  Purpose: To create/remove entries in the unicast port map
           (N sessions per message)
  Parameters:
    - action (create or remove)
    - number of sessions
    - udp port start
    - Session type: SPTS muxing, MPTS passthru, MPTS muxing, data injection
  Return:
    - status (OK)
  Note: current we assume a continuous range of UPD port.  May need to extend
        if this proves to be insufficient for some mapping table that we need
        to support.


Multicast Session Config / Unconfig
  Purpose: To create/remove an entry in the multicast lookup table
           (one session per message)
  Parameters:
    - action (create or remove)
    - multicast mode? (ASM, SSM)
    - source/dest IP, dest UDP
    - Session type: SPTS muxing, MPTS passthru, MPTS muxing, data injection
  Return:
    - status (OK, not supported)


Video Input Session Configuration
  Purpose: To add an video input session

  Parameters:
    - Input type: unicast or multicast
      - For unicast, we need dest UDP port (IP address needed?)
      - For multicast, we need source and dest IP, and dest UDP port

  Return: MB Video SW will return the session ID created.


