- Need to be able to temporarily disable (or mute) an input port


Video input session provision
  Purpose:
    To provision an input port in the unicast/multicast lookup table,
    and create and setup the input session struct

  Parameters:
    - input type: unicast or multicast
    - dest IP address
    - src IP address (0.0.0.0 if don't care)
    - dest UDP port
    - src UDP port (0 if don't care)
    - process type: SPTS remux, MPTS passthru, MPTS remux, data injection
    - 
    - max bitrate (0 if unknown)
    - enable (if 1, enable the input port immediately)

  Return: session ID


Video input session program selection
  Purpose: 
    To specify a set of MPEG programs to be accepted
    (Without this message, all input programs are accepted by default)

  Parameters:
    - in session ID
    - enable (if 1, enable the input port immediately)
    - number of program number
    - array of program number


Video input PID filter
  Purpose
    To specify a set of PIDs to be dropped at input
    (Without this message, no PID other than NULL and PSI will be dropped)


Video output session provision
  Parameters:
    - input session ID
    - QAM ID
    - program number (SPTS only)


